channels.description_long:
Big Beat came out of England in the early to mid-1990s and became one of the first widely embraced electronic music exports to the United States. Made popular by artists like Fatboy Slim, The Prodigy, and The Chemical Brothers, Big Beat proved that electronic music – other than Trance – could fill stadiums and large venues just as well as the rock and pop artists of the time. While the sound reached its peak between 1995 and 1999, the DI.FM Big Beats channel is keeping it alive and well today with a perfect curation of sounds from the past combined with today’s best contributions to the subgenre.
True to its name, Big Beat focuses on fat, heavy beats while adding in sampled loops from other genres including rock, pop, punk, jazz, funk, soul and more. Most tracks fall within a mid-tempo range of 90 to 120 BPM. Another defining characteristic that keeps Big Beat fans on the edge of their seats is the variety of sounds and samples that are often layered into the tracks including rap, punk, or pop-style vocals, exotic instruments, sirens, film and TV dialogue samples, and more.
channels.description_short: Heavily focused on breakbeats and dusty samples. A defining 90s musical movement still going strong today.
channels.name: Big Beat
channels.description: Heavily focused on breakbeats and dusty samples. A defining 90s musical movement still going strong today.

channels.description_long: Big Room House exploded onto the American music scene around 2009-2010 and gained overnight mainstream popularity. It is arguably the most commercialized subgenre of EDM, but who can resist it? The music follows a predictable but outrageously addictive recipe with long trancey build-ups that climax with an impossible-to-miss electro-style drop, most often followed by a 4/4 hard-style kick that serves as the official stamp of Big Room House authenticity. Martin Garrix’s No. 1 selling track, “Animals” is a defining example of the sound. Big Room House gained immortal fame within the electronic music world as artists like Hardwell, KSHMR, Nicky Romero, Blasterjaxx, Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike, Tiësto, and R3HAB released popular tracks that made the sound part of their musical styles.
channels.description_short: Fusing together house elements from the past and the present - prime time music full of uplifting high energy.

Since their early days, Breakbeats have gone on to contribute widely to other subgenres of electronic music. The Breaks sound can be heard in styles including Drum & Bass, Big Beat, Jungle, Dubstep, UK Garage, and even Hardcore. The DI.FM Breaks music channel brings together the best of pure Breaks sounds with creative synths and effects.

channels.description_long: “Tropical House” was a term coined in 2013 by Tom Jack Johnston, better known by his stage name Thomas Jack. The Australian DJ, record producer and musician at first used the term somewhat jokingly, but it caught on quickly and is now known around the world and heard every summer at top music festivals like Tomorrowland. In addition to Thomas Jack, the style was made popular by artists like Kygo, Matoma, Lost Frequencies, Seeb, and Klingande. The sunny, relaxed feel of the music comes from tempos that are a little slower than deep house at 110-115 bpm and the lack of the pumping compression-effect of big room style house music. Tracks on the DI.FM Chill & Tropical House music channel often include tropical instruments such as steel drums, guitar, pan flute, or marimba that create an uplifting feeling like a mini vacation every time you tune in.

channels.description_long: On the far end of the Techno spectrum, past the mainstream and niche-trendy, and deep into the hardest, darkest alley of the genre lies Gabber. This music is only for the hardest of hardcore Techno fans and not recommended for the faint-of-anything. Born in the late 80’s out of an ultra-industrial form of Belgian New Beat techno, Gabber found a home in Rotterdam, whose gritty fans embraced it as an opposition anthem to the more pretentious house scene in Amsterdam. Gabber music is characterized by highly distorted bass drum samples, scathing synths, and relentless percussion. It’s been called the ‘death metal’ of electronic music and has such a zealous following that there are apparently dating sites dedicated solely to those whose ears are tuned for Gabber’s smashing sounds. While Gabber is best served loudly in an abandoned warehouse somewhere in the Netherlands, the DI.FM Gabber channel is your next best option, curated by one of its most dedicated fans and updated regularly to bring you the latest and greatest each day.
channels.description_short: The hardest form of techno with punishing tracks designed to drive the crowds into a sweaty frenzy.

channels.description_long: The exact definition of hard dance can be debated ad infinitum, so we’ll stick to telling you what we offer. The DI.FM Hard Dance channel curates only the best tracks from around the world that cover the sounds of Hard Trance, Hard House, and the harder side of Eurodance – all with danceable beats, concrete kicks, and punching rhythms meant to keep you moving all night.  If you’re looking for a euphoric experience, begone. Here you’ll find the heavy, head-pounding, aggressive beats that make your body jump. channels.description_long: By our definition, Hard Techno is one step closer to the dark side than Hardcore. The music heard on the DI.FM Hard Techno channel is tough-as-nails warehouse jams full of cold aggression, sinister structures and pounding rhythms that hit hard. After Hardcore was born in the 70s and 80s, this extremely hard style of techno emerged and became popular in the Netherlands. It features heavy distortion, high tempos in the 160+ bpm range, and prominent kickdrums that excluded it from club scenes but made it a must-have at late-90s raves. While it tends to be more popular in Europe still to this day, the driving industrial sound has won over a diverse group of listeners around the globe.
channels.description_short: Tough as nails warehouse jams full of cold aggression, sinister structures and pounding rhythms that hit hard.
channels.name: Hard Techno
channels.description: Tough as nails warehouse jams full of cold aggression, sinister structures and pounding rhythms that hit hard.

channels.description_long: Hardcore music defines the darker and more menacing side of Techno. With a history that can be tracked back as early as the 1970s – before the explosion of artistic creativity that brought us many of electronic music’s more nuanced styles – Hardcore Techno boasts a true OG status in the genre, although the style is said to have become more officially defined much later-on in the early 90s. The music stands apart from mainstream Techno with faster tempos in the 160 – 200+ bpm range, and a heavily industrial sound that gives it a much more aggressive and gritty sound. Like the rest of Techno’s darker sounds, it was born out of the Belgian New Beat industrial style of Techno. The DI.FM Hardcore channel is curated by hand to bring you the best tracks that embrace the fast-paced go-hard style from around the world.
channels.description_short: Strictly for the hardcore. These are the biggest and boldest bangers, and the hardest hitting tracks.
channels.name: Hardcore
channels.description: Strictly for the hardcore. These are the biggest and boldest bangers, and the hardest hitting tracks.

channels.description_long: For those who love the harder sounds of electronic music but can’t quite embrace the intensity of sounds like Hardcore and Gabber, we present the DI.FM Hardstyle channel. Hardstyle was developed around the turn of the century as a more crowd-pleasing alternative to Hardcore, Hard House, and Gabber which were too industrial, repetitive, fast and invasive for many clubs and rave scenes. The music fuses elements of Hard House, Hard Trance, and Hardcore and is most notably defined by the inclusion of reverse bass, heavy kick bass, and screeches. Dedicated fans will tell you that tempos increased from the 135-150 bpm range in the early Hardstyle days to the 150-160 bpm range that’s more commonly heard today. High-tempo melodies bring the tracks to life and create the euphoric effect that revelers love while still maintaining deep roots in the industrial grit of EDM.
channels.description_short: Hard techno & hardcore. A global phenomenon with powerful kicks, distorted effects and infectious melodies.
channels.name: Hardstyle

channels.description_long: When House music emerged from Chicago’s underground club scene in the early 1980’s, no one would have been able to predict the momentous force it would exert on evolution of electronic music as a whole. In many ways, the story of House is the story of Chicago itself – a gritty mixture of musical styles and cultures, influenced by a hard and diverse windy city that almost demands new things to evolve out of the old. DJs seeking fresh sounds for the club scene sampled the sounds around them including rap, jazz, Latin music, synth pop, and more, setting them to the repetitive four-on-the-floor rhythms and deep basslines that define House music to this day. Tracks often include sampled vocals, and usually maintains a tempo between 110 and 130 bpm to keep bodies moving to the music all night long. The DI.FM House music channel brings together the best music from the global phenomenon that House has become for your pure listening pleasure.
channels.description_short: Born in Chicago and now global, house music is always evolving but remains true to its pure 4/4 structure.

channels.description_long: Raving has been around for a number of years – and while the laser beams, fast-moving beats, all-out battles on the dance floor, and energetic crowds haven’t changed much, the music has certainly evolved into a new genre. With Oldschool Rave, you can go back to your roots with a radio channel that only plays the famous sounds that you knew when raving was completely new to you. Take it back to the origins of rave music and lose yourself in nostalgia – but keep on dancing just like you always have.
channels.description_short: Grab your whistles, white gloves and reach for the laser beams. This is the sound of raving when raving was new.
channels.name: Oldschool Rave
channels.description: Grab your whistles, white gloves and reach for the laser beams. This is the sound of raving when raving was new.

channels.description_long: Techno and trance music have their place in history – as do the many tracks and beats that have gone through the genres in the years past. Today, you can be the time traveler that you’ve always wanted to be and go back in time to listen to the biggest and best tracks within both techno and trance. Give yourself the history lesson that you need to learn all about the tracks that defined a decade of dance culture all around the world. This radio channel is perfect for those who love throwbacks, or for those who simply want to know what it was like when it all started. Lose yourself in a whirlwind of our favorite techno and trance tracks all day long.
channels.description_short: Go back in time and hear the biggest and best tracks within techno and trance that defined a decade of dance culture.
channels.name: Oldschool Techno & Trance
channels.description: Go back in time and hear the biggest and best tracks within techno and trance that defined a decade of dance culture.

channels.description_long: Just as the name connotes, Progressive electronic music is the sub-genre that categorizes the artists that are moving the music forward. By nature, it changes with time, but Progressive electronic generally means the sounds are coming from untapped and atypical sources – sometimes new technologies, sometimes old ones being used in new ways. Progressive artists tend to create their own sounds, so if you hear familiar samples they’re always presented in surprisingly new and creative ways. With so much music out there calling itself by this name, the DI.FM Progressive channel is the best place to hear only the finest music from new trailblazers and well-known Progressive artists.
channels.description_short: Always moving forward, progressive continues to reinvent itself into new sounds and styles made for the floor.
channels.name: Progressive
channels.description: Always moving forward, progressive continues to reinvent itself into new sounds and styles made for the floor.

channels.description_long: Ready to step into an undiscovered world of psychedelic dimensions, pulsating beats, and progressive rhythms? When you’re ready to take the plunge, the DI.FM Progressive Psy radio channel is waiting to blow your mind. Sit back, relax and let the music take control, with trippy, progressive psy beats that pack a punch. With a curated tracklist hand-selected by our in-house progressive psy fanatic, everything you need for your psychedelic journey is right at your fingertips. All you need to do is open your mind and push play.
channels.description_short: Progress your mind to undiscovered psychedelic dimensions.
channels.name: Progressive Psy
channels.description: Progress your mind to undiscovered psychedelic dimensions.

channels.description_long: Ever wondered what happens when you take the electronic sounds and atmospheric textures of ambient music then put them through a trippy, psychedelic spin cycle? The result is Psybient, and it needs to be heard first hand in order to be fully experienced. We put together a Psybient radio channel to make it easier for adventurous listeners to do exactly that. Featuring a cutting-edge selection of psychedelic ambient beats, Psybient radio is the perfect gateway to the genre. Transport your mind, body, and spirit to a deeper plane of existence today.
channels.description_short: The psychedelic side of ambient.
channels.name: Psybient
channels.description: The psychedelic side of ambient.

channels.description_long: With PsyChill radio, the perfect soundtrack to your next chillout session is always right at your fingertips, ready to get your head nodding as it relaxes your body and boosts your mood. This curated selection of PsyChill favorites combines downtempo psychedelic dub grooves with world beats and goa ambient. The result? A playlist so chilled out you can use it to keep your drink cold, but psychedelic enough to open your mind to a whole new world. Push play whenever you’re ready to experience this trippy, one of a kind PsyChill journey first hand.
channels.description_short: Downtempo psychedelic dub grooves, goa ambient, and world beats.
channels.name: PsyChill
channels.description: Downtempo psychedelic dub grooves, goa ambient, and world beats.

channels.description_long: Ready to embark on a journey into atmospheric sounds, melodic basslines, and hypnotic samples? PsyDub fuses elements from psychedelic trance with ambient and dub music, drawing heavily on samples that reference space exploration, time travel and other out of this world topics. DI.FM PsyDub radio channel is your ticket to a mind-blowing new world of music, serving as a great intro to PsyDub for new listeners, and comfort food to fans who already love the genre.
channels.description_short: Dub, ambient, and psychedelic trance, fused together in atmospheric harmony.
channels.name: PsyDub
channels.description: Dub, ambient, and psychedelic trance, fused together in atmospheric harmony.

channels.description_long: Hockey players, classic novelists and fine vodka are great, but we think Russia’s greatest cultural export over the past century has been dance music. We have compiled some of our favorite Russian club hits into this radio channel so that the whole world can experience the best of the genre. These club bangers might have originated in Moscow and St. Petersburg, but with the push of a button, they can now be heard in Toronto, Tel Aviv, and London, or anywhere else across the globe. Add some Russian Club Hits to the mix and take your party to the next level.
channels.description_short: Russia's hottest club hits.
channels.name: Russian Club Hits
channels.description: Russia's hottest club hits.

channels.description_long: When warm, feel-good soul vibes mesh with melodic house beats the result is a blissful, happy explosion of sound that sends waves of joy throughout your entire existence – mind, body, and spirit. We’ve captured this feeling, and compiled it into a soulful house radio channel featuring uplifting tracks from some of the world’s premier DJ’s. Packed with vibrant melodies, enchanting vocals, and captivating vibes, this selection is all but guaranteed to get your toes tapping and head nodding, but to be honest, it’ll probably get you up and dancing too.
channels.description_short: House music saturated with feeling – full of melodies, vocals and true soul. Steady warm 4/4 vibes.
channels.name: Soulful House
channels.description: House music saturated with feeling – full of melodies, vocals and true soul. Steady warm 4/4 vibes.

channels.description_long: The DI.FM Space Dreams channel takes you on journeys measured in lightyears where your mind is free to imagine unexplored galaxies and worlds nothing like our own. Our dedicated curater sifts through endless piles of spacey tracks to bring you only the best music in the scene with a special emphasis on music you can drift to sleep to. After the first few perfectly ambient tracks, you’re almost guaranteed to completely mentally relaxed and falling asleep peacefully for a mid-day nap or a peaceful night’s rest. Journey with us to the outer edges of the universe and enjoy the entrancing sounds of deep space, perfect for emptying your mind, studying, relaxing, or practicing mindfulness and meditation.
channels.description_short: Ambient space music for expanding minds.
channels.name: Space Dreams
channels.description: Ambient space music for expanding minds.

channels.description_long: Whether your looking for something to play while you’re chilling out poolside or looking to play something that makes you feel like you’re chilling out by the poolside even when you aren’t, this Summer Chill House radio channel puts summer vibes right at your fingertips. These mellow, chill house beats pair perfectly with exotic drinks, good times and warm weather, but they can also help brighten up dark, winter days too. Whatever the season, this Summer Chill House radio channel will help you chill out, relax and unwind. Push play and start your summer chillout session right now.
channels.description_short: This selection of summer chill house classics has been handpicked to elicit that special summer feeling year-round.
channels.name: Summer Chill House
channels.description: This selection of summer chill house classics has been handpicked to elicit that special summer feeling year-round.

channels.description_long:
Influenced by video games and movie soundtracks of the 1980’s, Synthwave is the perfect blend of retro with modern sounds. There’s a reason for why the sounds of the 80s continue to remain relevant in pop culture and in the music scene – because sounds of the synth are unique and one of a kind. Synthwave takes all of the best aspects of the 80s aesthetic and repackages it into something entirely new and modern.
It’s as if the 80s have returned with a vengeance. Check out Synthwave today for a throwback like no other.
channels.description_short: Influenced by video games and movie soundtracks of the 80s, Synthwave's mission continues today with great new music keeping things future retro.
channels.name: Synthwave
channels.description: Influenced by video games and movie soundtracks of the 80s, Synthwave's mission continues today with great new music keeping things future retro.

channels.description_long: The DI.FM Tech House channel blends the warm harmonies and grooves of house music with the cold steely beats and rugged baselines of techno. It’s a musical yin and yang combination that has won the hearts of millions of fans across Europe and the Americas since the late 1990s and has recently made a resurgent comeback on the scene. The music emerged from prominent artists out of Spain and originally had a relatively minimal and clean production style that came from the techno scene of Detroit and the UK combined with the jazzy and soulful sounds of house.
channels.description_short: Blending the warmth of house music with the cold structural precision of techno, tech house bridges the divide.
channels.name: Tech House
channels.description: Blending the warmth of house music with the cold structural precision of techno, tech house bridges the divide.

channels.description_long: Techno music was born in the gritty, hard-working city of Detroit in the mid-to-late 1980s. It’s robotic and mechanical with artists using electronic instruments including synthesizers, drum machines, and sequencers to achieve the desired industrial sounds that define the genre. At the same time, Techno maintains its soul with the melding of the futuristic, techy sounds with electropop, house, and funk. Tempo is usually kept at a healthy 120 to 150 bpm, with most tracks learning toward the more heart-racing paces. A unique characteristic of Techno is that much of the music is produced for use in a continuous DJ set, which explains why this channel also offers a library in the hundreds of mix shows to enjoy.  Tune in to the DI.FM Techno Channel to hear arguably one of the world’s greatest collections of exceptional Techno tracks from the U.S., U.K., Germany, and beyond.
channels.description_short: Techno is a true musical force full of structure and style. Robotic, mechanical and full of soul, always facing the future.
channels.name: Techno
channels.description: Techno is a true musical force full of structure and style. Robotic, mechanical and full of soul, always facing the future.

channels.description_long: Trance is pure, emotive dance music which embraces incredible melodies, future-facing production and energetic anthems that have made it a pillar of electronic music worldwide. Its instantly recognizable 4/4 beat combines with rifting and psychedelic qualities that draw fans to the dancefloor and leave them begging for more at the end of the night.  In addition to 24/7 streaming, this channel brings you exclusive, and unique Mix Shows from the top DJs in Trance including Armin van Buuren, Above & Beyond, Ferry Corsten, Paul van Dyk, and many more. And have no fear, although Trance has gone mainstream, the DI.FM Trance channel brings together only the most epic sounding tracks from authentic artists without ever wandering near the realm of modern pop.
channels.description_short: Emotive dance music which embraces incredible melodies, future-facing production and energetic anthems heard worldwide.
channels.name: Trance
channels.description: Emotive dance music which embraces incredible melodies, future-facing production and energetic anthems heard worldwide.

channels.description_long: Born out of the southern hip-hop scene in Atlanta, trap combines bass-heavy rap beats with techno influences, and the result is a booming explosion of innovative sounds guaranteed to get your speakers rocking. Featuring analog drum machines, DnB rhythms, and an old school, dirty south hip-hop aesthetic, our trap radio channel boasts a curated collection of hand-selected beats that are perfect for rattling the speakers in the club, the trunk of a Cadillac or your speakers. With DI.FM’s Trap Radio, the pulsating hip hop beats of Atlanta, Memphis, and Houston have truly gone global.
channels.description_short: Born out of Southern Hip-Hop and influenced by techno, trap is analog drum machines / DnB & with hip-hop aesthetics.
channels.name: Trap
channels.description: Born out of Southern Hip-Hop and influenced by techno, trap is analog drum machines / DnB & with hip-hop aesthetics.

channels.description_long: If you like the percussive side of house music, then you’ll love the hand-picked selection of drum-heavy beats on DI.FM’s Tribal House radio channel. This popular subgenre of house music incorporates indigenous world music into the mix, creating a raw, original sound that places drums front and center. Often accompanied by hypnotic, rhythmic chanting, Tribal House is proof that the music of Africa, Asia, and Latin America can live on for eternity when infused with modern club music. Push play to travel through time and journey across the globe with Tribal House today.
channels.description_short: The percussive side of the house and tech house scene, tribal house takes drums and puts them in the forefront.
channels.name: Tribal House
channels.description: The percussive side of the house and tech house scene, tribal house takes drums and puts them in the forefront.

Once you push play and listen to their award-winning content, you’ll understand why we are so excited to collaborate with UMF.

From the streets of Berlin to the alleyways of Brooklyn, Underground Techno is a soundtrack made by the real underground artists who are grappling for turf, for the airwaves, and for their claim on the music scene. Embracing the traditional conventions of techno music, Underground Techno offers something new – real techno created by real artists – not computers and not big-name musicians with teams of producers by their side.
This is what’s really happening out there on the street – give it a listen today.

channels.description_long: Chillout offers fans a musical experience with a slow tempo and relaxed mood. The name for the music is said to be initially coined by Heaven Nightclub in 1989 where “chill-out music” was played in The White Room by DJs spinning ambient mixes meant to help dancers relax. The DI.FM Vocal Chillout radio channel makes it easy to find the best music out of the sea of content that now exists calling itself “chillout.” Our dedicated curator, Solarsoul, spends countless hours sifting through new tracks from around the globe and thousands of demo submissions to bring you the freshest new content in Vocal Chillout on a regular basis. We guarantee this channel will serve up tracks you’ll love with silky smooth vocals that calm your senses and ease your mind.
channels.description_short: Relaxing vibes and a collection of vocal songs providing the laid back soundtrack to your day.
channels.name: Vocal Chillout
channels.description: Relaxing vibes and a collection of vocal songs providing the laid back soundtrack to your day.

When it’s time to feel the energy, bring that human element back into play for a real listening experience.

Featuring a mind-blowing selection curated by our in-house vocal lounge expert, these tracks blend angelic vocals with rhythmic, pulsating lounge beats. The result? A smooth, sensuous, musical experience that will chill you out, calm you down, and transport you to a whole new world of possibilities. Sit back, relax and enjoy the ride.

Vocal Trance music is characterized by energetic tempos (usually between 110 – 150 bpm), pioneering production quality, and seductive musical tension that builds throughout the tracks culminating in the drops that leave fans in love and wanting more. Laced throughout each track on the DI.FM Vocal Trance channel, you’ll enjoy ethereal and soaring vocals that add depth and beauty to the music. In our quest to bring you the best and freshest Vocal Trance from around the world, this channel offers an impressive collection of mix shows that include exclusive and first-to-air content only found on DI.FM.
